<DOC><DOCNO> AP881028-0126 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-10-28-88 1236EDT</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--Malaysia-UN     10-28 0089</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--Malaysia-UN,0091</SECOND><HEAD>Malaysian Schools Will Close to Celebrate U.N. Seat</HEAD><DATELINE>KUALA LUMPUR, Malaysia (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Prime Minister Mahathir Mohamad onFriday declared a school holiday next week to celebrate the nation'snew seat on the U.N. Security Council.   The U.N. General Assembly elected Malaysia this week to succeedJapan in a two-year Security Council term beginning Jan. 1.   The prime minister said the selection represents a greatinternational victory for this southeast Asian country. To mark it,all schools will be closed Monday across the nation, he said.</TEXT></DOC>